<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaydar on Memorandum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402152594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1514 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Kulbitskiy] </F>
  [Text] St. Augustin, Germany February 24 TASS--Yegor Gaydar 
described the "memorandum of accord" adopted by the majority of 
the State Duma on Wednesday as a resolution towards escalation 
of tension in Russia, destabilisation of state authority and 
creation of prerequisites for civil war. The leader of Russia's 
Choice parliamentary faction spoke here on Thursday at a 
colloquium "the Future of Reform in Russia" organised by the 
Konrad Adenauer Foundation. 
  Gaydar said special anxiety is caused by the fact that under 
the decision of the State Duma not only politicians involved in 
plots and coups but also such characters as Barkashov, Anpilov, 
Terekhov and their associates will be absolved of 
responsibility. "I do not have the slightest doubt that upon the 
release from custody these people will resort to their former 
activity and will exert every effort to destabilise the 
situation and unleash bloody clashes in Moscow again on May 1 
and 2, 1994", Gaydar said. He believes that chances for calm 
democratic development in Russia decreased considerably and 
Russian democracy is threatened. 

</TEXT>

