<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Worried Over Local Election Campaign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502114094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1107 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502114094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 25 TASS -- The State Duma (lower 
house of the Russian parliament) adopted an address on Friday to 
the Russian president, as the guarantor of the Russian 
Constitution, requesting him to use his powers to ensure 
constitutionality during the election campaign to bodies of 
state authority in member republics of the Russian Federation 
and to bodies of local self-government. 
  The Duma's address to the president was prompted, above all, 
by concern over facts of discrepancy between this process and 
provisions of the Russian Constitution and the lack of adequate 
control over the observation of legality from federal bodies of 
power. 
  Lawmakers were especially concerned over violations of 
voting 
rights of citizens in legal acts adopted by bodies of state 
power in member republics of the Russian Federation, infringing 
on the principles of equal suffrage and restricting the 
participation of citizens and their associations in the election 
campaign as well as over violations of the principle of openness. 
  The Duma's address was also sent to parliament's upper 
chamber, the Russian Government, bodies of state authority in 
member republics of the Russian Federation, the Russian 
procurator-general and the Russian Central Electoral Commission. 
The address calls on them to take measures "to implement 
successfully new state construction in Russia by concerted 
efforts of all interested sides". 

</TEXT>

