<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peacekeeping Forces Keep North Ossetia Calm </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402170894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1602 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz February 24 TASS--The situation in the 
regions of North Ossetia where state of emergency has been 
extended until March 31, remains relatively calm, according to 
well informed military sources. 
  No clashes and conflict situations on the inter-ethnic 
grounds have been reported over the last twenty-four hours. The 
peacekeeping forces of Russia continue to fulfill tasks on 
maintaining state of emergency. 
  The same sources confirm that the crime situation in the 
region is still very tense. Over 3,000 vehicles were examined 
on the territory of North Ossetia. Seven units of firearms, 
grenades and hundreds of cartridges of a different caliber were 
confiscated from local inhabitants by patrol squads. 
  More than one hundred trains were checked up and escorted at 
railway stations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

