<H3> <TI>   New Far East Political Movement Set Up </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402133294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1159 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yevgeniy Lents] </F>
  [Text] Vladivostok February 24 TASS -- The presentation of 
a new public and political movement Russian Far East was held 
today in Vladivostok, the administrative centre of the Maritime 
territory. It was created on the initiative of a group of 
deputies to the State Duma from the Yabloko group, who are now 
touring the Far East. 
  Speaking at the presentation, leader of the Yabloko 
parliamentary group Grigoriy Yavlinskiy stressed: "We are 
pinning much hope on the new movement, which should rally the 
reform-minded forces in the far eastern region of Russia." 

</TEXT>

