<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Satisfied With Draft Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2402200894 Tallinn BNS in English 1548 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2402200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Feb 24, BNS -- Flying to Latvia Wednesday 
[23 February], Polish President Lech Walesa transmitted a 
greeting to Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas when the 
plane was above Lithuanian territory. 
  The Polish president expressed satisfaction that "our 
foreign 
ministers have completed preparatory work for the signing of the 
agreement on friendly relations and neighborly cooperation 
between the republics of Lithuania and Poland." 
  The accord had been under negotiation for one and a half 
years. Lithuania and Poland completed the talks Tuesday in 
Warsaw. 
  So far there have been no reports as to the exact formulas 
chosen to mention the 1920-39 occupation of Vilnius and its 
region by Poland. 
  Vaclovas Domarkas, Lithuanian deputy minister of foreign 
affairs, said after the fifth and final round of talks that the 
treaty includes "historic moments which trouble us, but no 
specific names or dates." 
  According to unofficial reports, the accord says that 
Vilnius 
has always been the historic capital of the Lithuanian state. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-37972 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov038_v_94003" </HT>


