<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Second Unit at Ignalina Plant Shut Down </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402225294 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1700 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402225294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 20 February, a small increase in radioactivity 
was recorded by the Ignalina nuclear power station permanent 
control system in one of the unmanned hermetically sealed 
compartments of the second reactor. 
  This has been reported to ELTA by Viktor Shevaldin, director 
general of the Ignalina nuclear power station, today. 
  After additional investigation, a conclusion was made that 
radioactivity could have increased because of the leak of gas, 
which is used to pull the turbines, into this compartment. 
Although the rate of the gas leak was much lower than that 
permitted by the exploitation procedure, the administration of 
the station, however, decided to shut down the second power unit 
in order to be able to carry out a detailed inspection of the 
compartment and to eliminate the cause of the leak. 
  The unit is to be under maintenance from 25 February until 6 
March, Shevaldin said. The head of the power station also 
informed that the increase of radioactivity in the unmanned 
compartment of the second block did not have any influence 
either on the power station or on the radioactive background of 
the environment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

