<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy Delivers Letter of Support From Butrus-Ghali </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402123694 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 1000 
GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tajik </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Imamali Rakhmonov, head of state and chairman of the 
Supreme Soviet of the Republic of Tajikistan, yesterday met 
Ramiro Piriz-Baloon, UN secretary general's special envoy in the 
Republic of Tajikistan. 
  Ramiro Piriz-Baloon handed over to Imamali Rakhmonov a 
letter 
from UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali. The letter supports the 
measures taken by the leadership of Tajikistan to consolidate 
peace and promote national reconciliation. 
  Issues related to further stabilizing the situation in the 
country were discussed in the course of the meeting. 
  Rashid Olimov, minister of foreign affairs of the republic, 
and Karimjon Yuldoshev, state adviser to the head of state, took 
part in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

