<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   State of Emergency Prolonged in Areas Bordering Afghanistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502112594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1035 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe February 25 TASS -- The Tajik parliament 
ruled on Friday to prolong until July 1 the state of emergency 
in areas bordering on Afghanistan. 
  The state of emergency was initially introduced in January 
1993 and covers, in particular, the Shuroabad, Pyandzh, Shaartuz 
regions and the city of Khorog, the administrative centre of the 
Gorno-Badakhshan region. 
  According to the parliamentary decree, the state of 
emergency 
was prolonged for the sake of "stabilisation of the political 
situation in the above-mentioned areas, safety of residents 
living there, as well as in connection with incessant armed 
provocations on the Tajik-Afghan border". 

</TEXT>

