<H3> <TI>   Assembly Chairman Discusses Cooperation With PRC Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202115494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1113 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Fedoruk] </F>
  [Text] Beijing February 22 TASS -- China's intention to 
base relations of friendship and goodneighbourliness with 
Turkmenistan on the five principles of peaceful co-existence was 
expressed by Qiao Shi, chairman of the standing committee of 
China's National People's Congress, during a meeting with 
Turkmen Mejlis Chief Sakhat Muradov, who is currently on an 
official visit here. 
  The Chinese parliament chief emphasised the need to broaden 
friendly cooperation between the two countries in politics, 
economics, science, technology, and culture. 
  Qiao pointed out a considerable strengtheing of contacts 
with 
foreign countries over the past 15 years, RENMIN RIBAO reported 
on Tuesday. This, he said, was resultant of an active 
realisation of reforms and the open-door policy. 
  The Chinese parliament chief said China cannot do without 
drawing on the experience of foreign countries in the 
development of democracy and economics. 
  "However, one should not copy foreign models. One should act 
in line with the country's current realities," Qiao said. 
  Muradov said Turkmenistan attaches much importance to the 
development of contacts with China, whose experience may prove 
useful for the development of the Turkmen economy, RENMIN RIBAO 
reported. 

</TEXT>

