<F P=102>  WS2402133294 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0600 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2402133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In an effort to provide the level of strength needed 
to ensure the proper combat readiness of the Ukrainian Armed 
Forces during the transition to a two year period of military 
service according to clause No. 26 of the law on general 
military obligation and service, Ukrainian President Kravchuk 
decreed to prolong the term of military service for six months 
for servicemen who had been drafted to service in 
September-December 1992 for 18 months of service and who are 
performing their service within the Ukrainian Armed Forces -- 
the Border Forces of Ukraine, the Internal Forces of the 
Ukrainian Ministry of Internal Affairs, and the Civil Defense 
Forces of Ukraine. 

