Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol -- In an interview with a UNIAN 
correspondent on 24 February, Crimea's President Yuriy Meshkov 
stated: "For the time being there is not going to be any 
reaction on the part of Crimea's authorities to Ukraine's 
Supreme Council resolution regarding conformity of the 
Autonomous Republic of Crimea's Constitution with Ukraine's 
Constitution and laws. There are more important concerns." 
According to Meshkov, the resolution "is inexpert from the 
legal point of view. Kiev is scarcely managing to destabilize 
the situation on the peninsula in this way," noted Crimea's 
president. 

