<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council of Defense Ministers Agenda Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402112394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1110 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 24 TASS -- The Council of Defence 
Ministers of the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) will 
hold a two-day meeting in Moscow. The meeting will open at 
15:00 on Thursday [24 February], ITAR-TASS learnt at the public 
information centre of the headquarters on coordination of 
military cooperation between the CIS member states. 
  The meeting agenda consists of five items, including the 
approval of regulations on the Council of Defence Ministers of 
CIS member states. The decision on setting up the Council was 
adopted at the Commonwealth summit in Minsk in February 1992. 
  Today's meeting will sum up the results of drafting the main 
issues for coordinating military construction in the CIS. 
  The meeting will also decide on the staff establishment of 
the headquarters on coordination of military cooperation. It is 
supposed that the headquarters' divisions will be staffed on a 
coordination basis. 
  Its staff will consist of 250 people, including 120 from 
Russia. The headquarters is charged with collecting, summerising 
and analysing open information on the military and political 
situation in the world and regions of interest to the CIS 
countries. 
  The headquarters will also concert efforts to give mutual 
aid 
in creating and developing national armed forces. 
  The situation on the Tajik-Afghan border has become a 
traditional item at defence ministers' meetings over the recent 
past. The present meeting will decide on additional measures to 
stabilise the situation there. 
  The ministers will also discuss the celebration of the 50th 
anniversary since the end of the second world war. Meeting 
participants are supposed to take two decisions: measures to 
prepare for the celebration of the victory anniversary and to 
hold a spartakiad of CIS Armed Forces. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

