<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputies Fail To Adopt New Electoral Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2402142194 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1100 
GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2402142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the House of Government in Minsk, the 13th 
session of the Belarusian Supreme Soviet continues its work. 
Deputies began their working day, as usual, with the 
miscellaneous section, which was followed by the registration -- 
279 people's deputies attended today's debate. After that, 
deputies returned to the issues that they began to discuss at 
yesterday's session -- draft legislation on local administration 
and the economy of the Republic of Belarus and new legislation 
on Supreme Soviet elections. While the first bill was approved 
quickly, clashes erupted over the second one, and as the result, 
it was submitted for further consideration. 
  Having done this, the deputies began to adopt one piece of 
legislation after another with renewed zeal. Thus, without 
special difficulties, the draft housing code of the Republic of 
Belarus, the draft program for housing development, and draft 
legislation of public roads were adopted. Issues connected with 
taxes, however, generated many disagreements among deputies. 

</TEXT>

