<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karimov Meets With Rakhmanov; Trade Agreement Signed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202174894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1500 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Shakhnoza Ganiyeva and Sadyr Ziyamukhamedov; from the </F>
"Novosti" newscast] 
  [Text] Imamali Rakhmanov, chairman of the Tajik Supreme 
Soviet, arrived in Tashkent on a short visit today. 
  Serious and painful problems of the Tajik economy were 
discussed at the talks with Uzbek President Islam Karimov at the 
palace of friendship among peoples. In the opinion of the two 
leaders, Tajikistan's economic problems can only be surmounted 
if the social and political situation is stable, 
  A bilateral agreement on trade and economic cooperation 
between Uzbekistan and Tajikistan was signed as a result of the 
talks. 
  The news conference held after the signing of the document, 
however, was dominated by political issues, among them the 
problem of settling military conflicts along the Tajik-Afghan 
border and the attitude towards the state of affairs in 
Afghanistan. 
  Referring to these issues, the heads of the two states 
replied that they adhered to a policy of non-interference in 
Afghanistan's internal affairs and that stability in Afghanistan 
could only be guaranteed if Afghanistan chooses in favor of a 
democratic development. 
  Islam Karimov said that the presence of Russia's 
peacekeeping 
forces here was essential to ensure calm in the whole Central 
Asian region. 

</TEXT>

