<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chornovil on Kravchuk Not Seeking Reelection </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402225394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1901 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402225394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vyacheslav Chornovil, the leader of the Ukrainian 
Popular Rukh, said the President Leonid Kravchuk's announcement 
that he will not run for presidency was a tactical gimmick. 
  He told Interfax-Ukraine that the statement of the 
president's press service made public Wednesday had not said 
anything of his unwillingness to run n the elections. What 
Kravchuk is doing, Chornovil thinks, is trying to foil the 
presidential elections, at least in June. 
  Chornovil was one of Kravchuk's rivals in the December 1991 
presidential elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-38005 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov038_a_94016" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-038 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

