<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Podoprigora Backs Sending Peacekeepers to Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502105594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0849 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 25 TASS -- "The use of peace-keeping 
forces to settle the conflict in Bosnia and Herzegovina is 
necessary," Vladimir Podoprigora, chairman of the upper chamber 
committee on international affairs, said in an interview with 
ITAR-TASS here on Friday. 
  He noted that he was in the Dniester area where there were 
hostilities between the Moldovan Government and the breakaway 
Dniester Republic, and in Nagorno-Karabakh. He also visited 
other "flash points" in the world and drew the conclusion that 
it is impossible, as a rule, to settle such conflicts without 
the participation of peace keepers. 
  The upper chamber committees on international affairs as 
well 
as on security and defence will discuss, at a joint sitting, the 
question on dispatching an additional military contingent to the 
U.N. Protection Force in Bosnia. 
  The committees will debate a request by the U.N. 
secretary-general addressed to the Russian president to send an 
additional military contingent to the U.N. Protection Force 
stationed in Bosnia and Herzegovina in connection with the 
conclusion of agreements on a peaceful settlement of the 
conflict and a ceasefire in the Sarajevo zone. 
  In compliance with the Russian Constitution, the province of 
the Federation Council (upper chamber of the Russian parliament) 
includes "the question on possible use of the Russian Armed 
Forces outside the territory of the Russian Federation". 
  The preliminary debate on the issue will be conducted by the 
committees which will submit their proposal to a plenary session 
of the upper chamber. The Federation Council will debate the 
question on dispatching an additional military contingent 
numbering 300 to participate in the U.N. Protection Force to 
ensure control over the implementation of the agreement on a 
peaceful settlement of the conflict. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

