<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hearing for Putchists Postponed to 1 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402164194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1604 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By CRIME PRESS correspondent Yuriy Shcherban] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 24 TASS--Another hearing on the case 
of those involved in the abortive coup, fixed for February 25, 
has been put off till March 1. This decision is not connected 
with the State Duma's resolution on amnesty for participants in 
the August 1991 events, adopted on Wednesday, CRIME PRESS 
learned from the military collegium of the Russian Supreme 
Court. The hearing was put off because of the continued illness 
of the wife of defendant Vasiliy Starodubtsev. She is in an 
intensive care unit of a hospital after a stroke. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

