<H3> <TI>   Radio, TV Association Suspended </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK2502085094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 25 Feb 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK2502085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Hold the Front Page!" </F>
rubric: "Federation Council Does Not Act Telegenically"] 
  [Text] The head of the Federation Council staff has 
directed that the operation of the International Association of 
Radio and Television [IART], based in the former House of the 
Russian Press, be discontinued. 
  Association employees who reported to work yesterday were 
not 
admitted into the building by security. They had their passes 
seized and were advised to take it easy until 1 March (when the 
Federation Council winds up its work), explaining that entry was 
denied them for their own safety. The employees were even 
barred from making sure their studio, with equipment worth more 
than 150 million rubles, was quite safe. The Federation Council 
apparatus does not seem to worry about how dozens of Association 
members up and down the CIS are going to get programming and how 
much IART losses will be -- chiefs of the Association cannot get 
any answer out of it. 

</TEXT>

