<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   CIA Delegation To Visit Moscow `Soon' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402133194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1316 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow February 24 -- According to reliable sources, 
high-ranking officials of the Central Intelligence Agency are 
due to arrive in Moscow from the United States soon to discuss 
the case of the Ames, a married couple charged with espionage in 
favour of the former Soviet Union and, later, Russia. 
  The U.S. President's spokeswoman Dee Dee Myers said on 
Wednesday [23 February] that the former leader of the CIA 
counterintelligence department targeting the Soviet Union, 
Aldrich H. Ames and his wife evoked suspicions some ten months 
ago and were closely watched by the Central Intelligence Agency 
and the Federal Bureau of Investigations until the American 
Administration took the case to court charging the two with 
espionage. 
  The exact date of the arrival of the American delegation is 
not yet known. It is likely that the CIA officials will wait 
for Russian external intelligence service chief Yevgeniy 
Primakov to return home from Prague. 
It is not ruled out that in view of the ballyhoo in the United 
States around the Ames affair, his former colleagues may ask for 
a prompt assignment with the leaders of the Russian intelligence 
service. 
  The press service of the U.S. Embassy in Moscow declined to 
comment at ITAR-TASS request on the forthcoming visit of CIA 
officials to Moscow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

