<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Team `Already Visited' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502101094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0955 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Washington February 25 TASS -- A U.S. daily said 
that a CIA team, which was reported to be only preparing for a 
trip to Moscow in connection with the arrest of Aldrich Ames on 
charges of spying for Kremlin, had already visited the Russian 
capital. 
  THE WASHINGTON POST said on Friday [25 February] that the 
CIA 
delegation failed to achieve what it had expected during the 
trip and is returning home. 
  In Moscow the Russian Foreign Intelligence Service refused 
either to confirm or deny the report. 
  Spokesman Boris Labusov told TASS that he has no necessary 
information to comment on THE WASHINGTON POST report. 

</TEXT>

