<H3> <TI>   Foreign Intelligence Chief Ends Visit to Slovakia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402222194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1720 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402222194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava February 24 TASS -- Russian Foreign 
Intelligence Chief Yevgeniy Primakov ended his visit to Slovakia 
on Thursday [24 February]. 
  He expressed satisfaction with the results of his talks in 
Bratislava, adding that both sides reiterated their willingness 
to develop mutual respectful relations between Russia and 
Slovakia. 
  During the visit, Primakov met with the leader of the Slovak 
Information Service, Vladimir Mitro, other officials to discuss 
ways to combat organised crime, international terrorism and 
illegal drug trafficking, as well as the situation in trouble 
spots. 
  Asked to comment on the spy scandal involving a senior CIA 
official, Aldrich Ames, and his wife arrested on charges of 
spying for the Soviet Union and then Russia for nearly a decade, 
Primakov replied "no comments," adding "but when I return to 
Moscow..." 

</TEXT>

