<H3> <TI>   Belarus Defense Minister Attends CIS Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602141694 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1300 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A session of the CIS Council of Defense Ministers 
has been held in Moscow. The Belarusian military delegation, 
headed by Colonel General Pavel Kazlowski, the republic's 
defense minister, examined and decided on questions concerning 
integration [words indistinct] of CIS countries in the military 
sphere. Primarily there was a discussion of documents 
regulating the activity of the coordination bodies of military 
cooperation -- the Council of Defense Ministers, its 
secretariat, and also the headquarters for coordinating military 
cooperation. 
  The defense ministers of Belarus and the Russian Federation 
signed an agreement on interaction of air defense forces and 
means. 
  The next session of the Council of Defense Ministers is 
planned for the middle period of March. It is intended that it 
will be held jointly with the CIS Council of Foreign Ministers. 

