<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministers Agree on Tajik Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502210594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1650 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chief of the Headquarters on Coordination and 
Military Cooperation between the CIS states, Serafim Yushkov 
approved of the decision on strengthening of the Tajik border 
adopted at the CIS defense ministers' meeting in Moscow on 
Friday. He suggested that military actions by Afghan Mojahedins 
and the armed Tajik opposition might become more active in 
spring. 
  According to Yushkov, the way from Afghanistan to Tajikistan 
will become easier due to opening of the mountain pass in spring. 
  The CIS defense ministers agreed to carry out the earlier 
agreements on stabilization of the situation on the Tajik-Afghan 
border. For instance, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Uzbekistan 
will bring their military contingency to Tajikistan. 
  The decision on the Tajik border is to be confirmed at the 
regular CIS summit planned for March 31. 

</TEXT>

