<H3> <TI>   Russian Embassy Has `No Comment' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602015694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0105 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602015694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Borisenko] </F>
  [Excerpts] Washington, 26 Feb -- The U.S. State Department 
declared Aleksandr Iosifovich Lysenko, counsellor in the Russian 
Embassy in the United States, "persona no grata." [passage 
omitted] ITAR-TASS has learned that Aleksandr Lysenko arrived 
in Washington in July 1993. He is 56 years old. The Russian 
Federation Embassy stated that "they had no comment on the State 
Department's statement." Immediately after the announcement by 
the State Department, a large group of American TV reporters and 
media photographers gathered at the Russian Federation Embassy, 
practically blocking the entrance to the building situated a few 
blocs away from the White House. Policemen who are permanently 
stationed at the Embassy are watching the developments with 
indifference. 

</TEXT>

