<H3> <TI>   `CIA Agent' Persona Non Grata </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802154494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1511 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Andrey Palariya and Vladimir </F>
Smelov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 28 Feb -- CIA agent James Morris, who worked 
in Moscow under the guise of a counsellor at the U.S. embassy, 
has been declared "persona non grata." 
  An ITAR-TASS correspondent was informed by reliable sources 
that an official statement about this was made today to U.S. 
ambassador in Moscow Thomas Pickering. The U.S. spy will leave 
Moscow within seven days. 
  This was Moscow's reaction to Washington's decision to expel 
Aleksandr Lysenko, counsellor at the Russian embassy, from the 
United States. 

</TEXT>

