<H3> <TI>   General Says Ames `Was of Benefit for Russia' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602190394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1855 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow February 26 TASS - "Ames worked in the United 
States for Russia. He protected Russian interests since he 
revealed spies stealing Russian secrets to the U.S. He 
inflicted no direct damage to the Americans and was of benefit 
for Russia," head of the Russian Armed Forces General Staff 
Colonel-General Mikhail Kolesnikov told a news conference here 
today, when asked about CIA officer Aldrich Hazen Ames charged 
with espionage in the Russian favor. 
  In his turn, commander of the Russian air-borne troops 
General Yevgeniy Podkolzin said there is no connection between 
the U.S. arrest of CIA officer Aldrich Hazen Ames and success of 
Russian diplomacy in settlement of Bosnian crisis. 

</TEXT>

