<H3> <TI>   General Staff Has `No Information' on Ames Links </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802112694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1118 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Polaria] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 28 TASS -- "The General Staff of the 
Russian Armed Forces and its intelligence service have no 
information on any links between the Ames couple and Soviet or 
Russian special services," Russia's Chief of Staff 
Colonel-General Mikhail Kolesnikov told ITAR-TASS on Monday. 
  He stressed that the U.S. mass media misinterpreted his 
statement on the Ames affair at the press conference on February 
26. "Such misinterpretations pursue one unseemly objective -- to 
get confirmation of the assumption that the CIA officer and his 
wife cooperated with the Soviet and Russian intelligence 
services". 

</TEXT>

