<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, Zlenko Agree To Boost Bosnia Political Settlement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502133394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1323 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Denis Perkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 25 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev and his Ukrainian counterpart Anatoliy Zlenko 
agreed during a telephone conversation on Friday that it is 
necessary to boost political settlement in Bosnia. 
  Kozyrev and Zlenko stressed the importance to ensure safety 
and most favourable conditions in order to help Russian and 
Ukrainian peace-keepers to fulfil their mission near Sarajevo 
and coordinate activities. 

</TEXT>

