<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Expresses Condolences to `Arafat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602143794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1251 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 26 Feb -- Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev 
was in touch with PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat today. He 
expressed condolences in connection with the tragic death of 
scores of totally innocent people in Hebron (al-Khalil), which 
has aroused the indignation of Palestinians, Arabs, and the 
entire Muslim world. We resolutely condemn this crime, the 
minister said. 
  Andrey Kozyrev expressed the hope that neither the 
Palestinians nor the Israelis would give in to the provocations 
of extremists and that the vigorous search for an all-embracing 
peace in the Near East would be continued. 
  In this connection Yasir 'Arafat stressed that he was 
interested in Russia's vigorous efforts. He requested the UN 
Security Council to support the Palestinian proposals. 
  Andrey Kozyrev replied that Russian representatives at the 
UN 
would urgently be given instructions on this score. They agreed 
to maintain day-to-day contact on these issues both by telephone 
and via diplomatic channels. 

</TEXT>

