<F P=103> LD2502183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Oslo February 25 ITAR-TASS -- Russian Defence 
Minister Pavel Grachev arrived here today on a working visit. 
At the airport he was welcomed by Norwegian Defence Minister 
Jorgen Kosmo. 
  The ministers discussed security in Northern Europe and 
possible bilateral cooperation of the armed forces on the Kola 
Peninsula. Grachev and Kosmo laid wreaths to the monument to 
Russian servicemen killed in Norway during the Second World War. 
  A meeting of Pavel Grachev and Norwegian Foreign Minister 
Bjorn Tore Godal focused on bilateral cooperation, ecological 
problems of the Novaya Zemlya and settlement of the Bosnian 
crisis. 
  Grachev will also visit the Norwegian parliament to meet 
heads of several parliamentary committees. On Saturday he will 
leave for Lillehammer to see the Winter Olympics. 

