<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on a statement signed by 40 people's 
deputies of the Belarusian Supreme Soviet, in which they refused 
to participate in the voting on the draft constitution, 
Vyacheslaw Kuznetsow, first deputy Supreme Soviet chairman, 
stated: "I think that the behavior of these people's deputies 
is very illogical, the more so since some of them were members 
of the Constitutional Committee. They have stated that they are 
against the form of voting. I, personally, believe that this is 
just an unwillingness to adopt the basic law," Vyacheslaw 
