<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich Criticizes Procedures for Constitutional Vote </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2802105894 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0400 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2802105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] I will either not vote at all or vote against it, 
because nobody has defined the subject of the voting, former 
Supreme Soviet Chairman Stanislav Shushkevich told an RID 
correspondent immediately after receiving his ballot for voting 
on three chapters of the Belarusian draft constitution. The 
point is that this is the wrong way to vote. It would be better 
to vote on separate chapters, and even better on separate 
articles. If the voting concerned separate articles, I would 
approve about 20 of them, the ex-speaker added. Asked why he 
did not join the statement signed by 40 deputies who refused to 
participate in the voting, Stanislav Shushkevich responded that 
he was simply not informed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

