<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich Calls For Early Presidential Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2702163894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1620 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2702163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM correspondent Nikolay Nazarovich for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Mogilev February 27 TASS -- Ex-speaker of the 
Belarusian Parliament Stanislav Shushkevich seems to have 
launched an election campaign for the republic's presidency. 
Over the past few days, he has been touring Belarusian cities 
and towns, calling for early presidential and parliamentary 
elections. 
  Shushkevich held at the weekend two meetings in Mogilev with 
the city's workers, stressing that "to make economic reforms in 
the country effective, democratic forces should unite on the 
basis of statehood, political and economic democracy, that is on 
the basis of transition to a free market". 
  Speaking about the merging of Russia's and Belarus' monetary 
systems, he came out for "a decent agreement, on equal terms, 
without any infringements upon Belarus' interests". 

</TEXT>

