<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Soviet Issues Decree on Regulating TV, Radio </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502213394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1756 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502213394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe February 25 TASS -- The Presidium of the 
Supreme Soviet of Tajikistan issued a decree on Friday on the 
regulation of television and radio broadcasting in Tajikistan. 
The two industries are now forbidden to use tv or radio time to 
propagandize or advertise erotic publications or alcoholic or 
tobacco products. They also may not broadcast programmes which 
conflict with the republic's national traditions or human moral 
norms. 
  In addition, until the adoption of a law on television and 
radio broadcasting, the draft of which is as yet only supposed 
to be worked out and discussed by the Supreme Soviet, the all 
television and radio studios which are not under state control 
are to be closed down and their wave lengths taken away 
throughout the entire Republic of Tajikistan. 
  It was emphasized that the decree was adopted in accordance 
with many requests received from the population of Tajikistan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

