<H3> <TI>   Says Tibet Always Part of China </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2901201294 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 29 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2901201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Qiao: `Tibet Will Continue To Be </F>
Part of China'"] 
  [Text] Vienna -- On Friday [28 January] President Thomas 
Klestil broached the human rights situation in China and the 
situation in Tibet in a talk with Qiao Shi, president of the 
Chinese parliament. This was stated in a handout of the 
President's Office. Reportedly, Qiao reaffirmed China's point of 
view that Tibet has always been part of Chinese territory. 
  In the parliament Qiao Shi had also affirmed that Tibet 
belongs to his country and declared that the Catholic Church is 
protected fully in the PRC. In a talk with members of the 
Bundesrat Presidium, the member of the CPC Political Bureau 
stated that the only condition for the Dalai Lama's return is 
his renunciation of Tibet's independence. 

</TEXT>

