<H3> <TI>   Claes To Sue Newspaper Over Agusta Allegations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3001140094 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in 
English 1330 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3001140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Foreign Minister Willy Claes intends to sue the 
newspaper HET LAATSTE NIEUWS for libel. The minister announced 
this in BRTN's Sunday morning [30 January] television program 
The Seventh Day. 
  HET LAATSTE NIEUWS yesterday wrote that Claes had been in 
favor of accepting a 15 million franc bribe from the Italian 
helicopter company Agusta. [passage omitted] 
  Minister Claes has fervently denied his involvement and says 
he never even discussed bribes with the Agusta company. 

