<H3> <TI>   Kohl Holds Talks With Finland's Salolainen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801202494 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1530 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Foreign Trade Minister Pertti Salolainen held 
talks in Bonn today with Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl on 
European integration. Salolainen, whom we contacted a short 
time ago, confirms that the European Commission has in practice 
completed its detailed stances on agriculture. 
  [Begin Salolainen recording] Well, yes, Federal Chancellor 
Kohl has the opinion that this is still fully possible [as 
heard] and he viewed very sympathetically the fact that Finland 
and the other countries applying for membership would become 
members in the European Union within this timeframe. In 
addition, he promised his full personal support, his strong 
support, toward the success of this. He saidthat this is 
necessary also regarding the general development in Europe, in 
other words, that a positive signal could be given to the rest 
of Europe about the fact that the European Union is a developing 
organization which can expand, and which would also be an 
example for the Central and East European countries, indicating 
that they, too, can progress further in the market economy and 
also toward future membership of the European Union. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

