<H3> <TI>   Hermes Guarantees for Arms Exports Triple in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2801143594 Duesseldorf WIRTSCHAFTSWOCHE in German 28 Jan 
94 p 8 </F>

<F P=103> AU2801143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Duesseldorf WIRTSCHAFTSWOCHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "cs": "Bonn Provides Massive Help"] </F>
  [Text] The Federal Government has increased its help to 
the ailing arms industry with Hermes export guarantees for 
international transactions. According to a confidential list of 
projects from the Finance Ministry in Bonn, in October 1993, 
government guarantees for military exports amounted to 2.3 
billion German marks -- three times more than in the previous 
year. 
  According to the list, which contains 10 projects, 
transactions with Indonesia account for more than half of the 
amount. The second major client is Turkey, which took the 
lion's share of Hermes guarantees for export deals in 1992. 
Both countries have promised billions in orders for German 
shipyards. In addition, the Federal Government provided several 
minor guarantees for the sale of helicopters of the Munich 
Messerschmitt-Boelkow-Blohm company to Botswana, Swaziland, 
Argentina, the Czech Republic, and the Philippines. 

</TEXT>

