<H3> <TI>   Corporate Cooperation Agreement Signed With Hungary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801111194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0944 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2801111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Budapest/Essen (ADN-WDO) -- The first cooperation 
project in the gas industry between Germany and Hungary has been 
signed in Essen by MOL Magyar Olaj-es Gazipari R.T., Budapest, 
and Ruhrgas AG. The two companies announced today that they 
will cooperate primarily in the purchase of natural gas from the 
West and its transport across Germany to Hungary. It has also 
been agreed that Ruhrgas will provide auxiliary supplies via a 
planned pipeline from Austria to Hungary, thereby improving the 
country's ability to ensure a constant and steady flow. 
  As part of the cooperation there are also plans to expand 
the 
infrastructure of the gas industry in Hungary and to introduce 
energy saving and environmentally friendly technology, including 
the installation of gasflow controlling and measuring equipment. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

