<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Robert Hue Elected New Communist Party Leader </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2901183994 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1800 
GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2901183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] At Saint-Ouen, site since last Tuesday [18 
January] of the 28th Congress of the French Communist Party, a 
new generation has taken over. The National Committee has made 
its choice, and as Alain Bocquet, MP [member of parliament] for 
the Nord [department] has just announced, it chose Robert Hue. 
Many people think that there will be no change. Robert Hue is 
known as a man of the Party apparatus, whose rise is relatively 
recent. [passage omitted] Robert Hue had been a member of the 
political bureau since the last Party congress in 1990. He is; 
nevertheless, an old communist, having joined the Party at 18, 
in 1964. [passage omitted] He is mayor of 
Montigny-les-Cormeilles [in the Val d'Oise department]. 

</TEXT>

