<H3> <TI>   Giugni Opens PSI Assembly; PSI To Link With AD </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2901120594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1115 GMT 
29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2901120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In his opening address at the "Italian Socialist 
Party (PSI) General Assembly", party chairman (Labor Minister 
Gino) Giugni was applauded when he told the 6,000 delegates in 
Rome that "the old Socialist Party leadership does not live here 
any more." He added: "That leadership" was responsible for "a 
destructive moral pollution" and for "a series of hastily taken, 
wrong political choices." 
  Before the assembly, Party Secretary (Ottaviano) Del Turco 
met Giorgio Bogi of the Democratic Alliance (AD). He told him 
that the PSI intends to stand together with the AD in the 
progressive alliance in the forthcoming general election. 

</TEXT>

