<H3> <TI>   Preparations for Discussion on CBM's Urged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3101103394 Nicosia ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 31 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> NC3101103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Opinions" column: "Preparation"] </F>
  [Text] Let us assume that UN Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali responds to President Glavkos Kliridhis' indirect 
suggestion to reject Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas' letter 
because the occupation leader's letter had the logo "Turkish 
Republic of North Cyprus, President's Office." 
  What will happen afterwards? Most likely, after exhibiting 
affecting manners, Denktas will reply to Butrus-Ghali on blank 
paper or even orally. And of course, he will tell him what he 
said in his second negative letter. That is, he will reply 
semi-positively to Butrus-Ghali's question of whether he agrees 
to discuss the confidence-building measures [CBM's]. 
  Therefore, the ball will be in our court again. We cannot 
throw it back, so we will start playing. That is, we will begin 
discussing the CBM's. This is approximately how ?hings will 
develop and this is why we must stop having illusions: We 
either participate in such a discussion or we do not. And if 
Kliridhis' stance so far has been to discuss the CBM's, then we 
must make preparations now. We must not lose any more time. 

</TEXT>

