<H3> <TI>   Clark Meets Other Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2801194494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2801194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special envoy 
for Cyprus, has been holding contacts in Ankara. 
  Joe Clark first met with Foreign Ministry Under Secretary 
Ambassador Ozdem Sanberk. In a statement he made prior to the 
meeting, Ambassador Sanberk stated that Turkey sees an 
atmosphere of insecurity in Cyprus, and therefore supports the 
confidence-building measures package. 
  Clark, in turn, stated that the solution to the Cyprus 
problem depends on the leaders of the two communities. Clark 
noted that he will submit a report to the UN secretary general 
concerning his visits to Cyprus, Greece, and Turkey. Clark 
further stated that he hopes Turkey will continue to extend its 
constructive help to find a solution to the Cyprus issue. 
  Clark later visited Foreign Ministry Deputy Under Secretary 
Tugay Ulucevik and conferred with him for some time. 

</TEXT>

