<F P=100> Turkey </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Officials Comment on Operation Against PKK </TI></H3>
<H4>   Team To Investigate Iranian Claims </H4>
<F P=102> TA3001153094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1502 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA3001153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Davos, Jan 30 (A.A) -- Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin on Sunday [30 January] said that a delegation will be set 
up to investigate allegations that nine civilians were killed 
and 19 wounded during Friday's air raid carried by the Turkish 
Armed Forces against terrorist bases in northern Iraq, near the 
Iranian-Turkish border. 
  Cetin said a "joint delegation" will go to Serdest [as 
received] village, in Iran, where allegedly civilians were hit. 
  He was speaking to an A.A. reporter in Davos where he was 
attending the World Economic Forum meetings. 
  He said he held two telephone conversations with his Iranian 
counterpart 'Ali Akbar Velayati on Saturday on the issue, adding 
he has reassured the latter that the strike was not directed 
against Iranian territory. 
  "According to Turkish military officials no harm should have 
been done in the region, but necessary action will be taken if 
it is determined by the committee that nine were killed and 19 
wounded," he said. 
  He said Iran has not asked for any compensation, but if 
there 
is such a case of civilians killed, Iran should be compensated. 

</TEXT>

