<F P=100> Turkey </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reporters Reportedly Kidnapped in Kurdish Area </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2901175894 Paris AFP in English 1503 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2901175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Jan 29 (AFP) -- Two reporters from the 
private Turkish television network TGRT were kidnapped in 
Kurd-dominated southeast Turkey, a senior TGRT official said 
Saturday [29 January]. 
  Kutlu Esendemir and Recep Ozturk had been preparing a 
television program in the region for the past week, TGRT 
official Erdal Celebi said. 
  The pair last contacted the network on Wednesday, when they 
left the Sulak police post in the Sirnak region, near the Iraqi 
border, heading toward Guclukonak, in the same region, Celebi 
said. 
  Celebi blamed the kidnapping on the Kurdistan Workers Party, 
the separatist movement which launched an armed rebellion 
against the Turkish government in 1984. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

