<F P=100> Turkey </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four `Terrorists' Die in Southeast </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2901180194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1448 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2901180194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, Jan 29 (A.A) -- Four terrorists from the 
outlawed separatist terrorist organization were killed and 24 
separatists were arrested in the southeast on Saturday [29 
January]. 
  The Emergency Regional Governor's Office told AA that the 
terrorists were killed in a clash with security forces in Genc 
township in Bingol and in Malazgirt township in Mus Province. 
  Twenty-four separatists who were responsible for aiding and 
abetting and providing logistic support to the terrorist 
organization were arrested in Adiyaman, Diyarbakir, Mardin, 
Sirnak and Van Provinces. 
  Meanwhile, three terrorists from the same organization 
surrendered to security forces in Silopi township in 
southeastern Sirnak Province. 

</TEXT>

