<H3> <TI>   Erbakan: Only Muslim Brotherhood Can End Terrorism </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2901200294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2901200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Prosperity Party [PP] leader Necmettin Erbakan has 
said that his party's mayoral candidates represent brotherhood, 
unity, and integrity, and that the PP will get all the mayoral 
positions in southeastern Anatolia after the 27 March local 
elections. 
  Addressing a party meeting in Ankara, Erbakan said the PP is 
the only party that is active in southeastern Anatolia, and that 
the parties imitating the West have been wiped out of this area. 
He stressed that the problem of terrorism can only be resolved 
through Muslim brotherhood. 
  [Begin Erbakan recording] It is impossible to end terrorism 
through the government's violent methods. The real solution to 
terrorism is the healing power of Muslim brotherhood, and this 
can be done only by the PP. After terrorism is healed, 60 
million people will get real human rights, real freedoms, and 
real justice. That is when happiness will be restored to our 
country. [end recording] 
  Erbakan charged that his party will come to power on its own 
at the end of the first general elections, and that at the end 
of the coming local elections it will get 1,000 mayoral 
positions in Turkey, including most of the positions in the 
greater Istanbul area. 
  Erbakan said: No one believes any more that this government 
will control the economy or defeat terrorism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

