<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spain Signs Frigate Accord With Netherlands, FRG </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2901204994 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1400 GMT 29 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2901204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the Dutch city of Maastricht, the Spanish 
secretary for defense has signed, alongside his German and Dutch 
counterparts, an international cooperation agreement for a 
program to construct F-100 class frigates. 
  According to this agreement, the Spanish Navy will obtain 
four new frigates. The construction of these frigates is to 
start in 1996 and they will be equipped with high-, medium-, and 
low-flying antiaircraft missiles, ground-to-ground missiles, and 
helicopters with air-to-ground missiles and torpedoes. 

</TEXT>

