<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkey's Demirel on Davos Contacts, Air Operation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2901071694 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0530 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2901071694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Metin Gokce in Davos] </F>
  [Text] President Suleyman Demirel, currently in 
Switzerland for the World Economic Forum meetings, proceeded 
from Zurich to Davos yesterday afternoon. He first attended a 
meeting on world economic developments in Davos. During the 
meeting, Demirel replied to various questions by representatives 
of leading business circles in the world. 
  In a news conference after the meeting, Demirel commented on 
his contacts. The president reported that during his contacts 
he explained that it is essential to reorganize Europe following 
the dissolution of the Soviet Union and that East European 
countries should be included especially in organizations such as 
NATO and the EC. Noting that he also stressed Turkey's 
importance for the EC, Demirel said Europe can stretch as far as 
Central Asia and China using Turkey as a bridge. He remarked 
that oil and natural gas from Central Asia will be transported 
to the Mediterranean via Turkey and underlined that Turkey will 
become an energy terminal in the future. 
  Answering a question on the air operation launched against 
the Zhalah camp, Demirel explained that the operation was 
conducted after long investigation. He declared that Zhalah had 
replaced the al-Biqa' Valley and 2,000 terrorists were sheltered 
in the camp. Great care was taken not to hurt women and 
children, Demirel added. 
  Demirel will continue his contacts and bilateral meetings in 
Davos today as well. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

