<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone report by Haluk Koc in Davos over still of map of </F>
Switzerland] 
  [Text] President Suleyman Demirel, who is in Davos for the 
World Economic Forum meetings, had breakfast with the presidents 
of the Central Asian Turkic republics and the prime minister of 
Pakistan. 
  Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev, Turkmen President 
Saparmurad Niyazov, Uzbek President Islam Karimov, and Pakistani 
Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto attended the breakfast. 
  In a statement after the breakfast, Demirel said that with 
