<H3> <TI>   Discusses Peres, 'Arafat Meetings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA3001201094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3001201094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Video report by Metin Gokce in Davos] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Speaking at a news conference 
today, President Suleyman Demirel said the following about his 
meetings with Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres and 
Palestinian head of state Yasir 'Arafat: 
  [Begin Demirel recording] I said that this is a golden 
opportunity that should not be missed. An enmity of 100 years, 
of at least 50 years, can be eliminated. This opportunity must 
be used well. Turkey supports all sides to achieve this. If 
closer support from our side is needed, we are ready to give it. 
However, if we interfere without being asked, we might further 
complicate this very difficult and complicated issue. I said 
the same thing to 'Arafat. [end recording] 
  Demirel said that at a meeting with Bulgarian Prime Minister 
Berov today, he stressed the importance of establishing regional 
peace and stability and building the east-west highway that will 
connect Istanbul to the Adriatic Sea over Bulgaria, Macedonia, 
and Albania. 
  At the meeting, Berov categorically denied the reports that 
the PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] terrorists expelled from 
certain European countries are basing themselves in Bulgaria. 
  Demirel also attended a meeting on Central Asia today. He 
ended his contacts in Davos today. After spending the night 
here, he will return to Turkey tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

