<H3> <TI>   Holds Investment Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101044194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3101044194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Davos, the prime minister has discussed 
multi-billion dollar investment projects in Pakistan with some 
industrial and investment teams from around the world. The 
prime minister's discussions centered around the construction of 
the (Lawari Tob) tunnel, to link Pakistan with Central Asia 
through Tajikistan; the establishment of rail and road links 
between Pakistan and Central Asia, to enhance global trade; 
setting up an industrial estate in Pakistan; and financing 
private thermal power units in Pakistan. 
  The Swedish prime minister, who met with Ms. Benazir Bhutto 
in Davos yesterday, discussed the expansion of bilateral 
cooperation. He expressed interest in possible investment in the 
(Lawari Tob) tunnel project, because this could greatly expand 
global trade with the regions of the former Soviet Union. Ms. 
Benazir Bhutto invited Swedish investors to invest in power 
plants in Pakistan. 
  Singapore Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew, during his meeting 
with the prime minister, emphasized his country's strong 
interest in investing in rail and road projects between Pakistan 
with Central Asia. Ms. Benazir Bhutto offered to let Singapore 
establish an industrial estate in Pakistan to help its 
industrial growth. Both leaders agreed to identify an effective 
means for transferring technology from Singapore to Pakistan. 

</TEXT>

