<H3> <TI>   Turkish President Blames Swiss for Embassy Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2901104694 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 0900 
GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2901104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Turkey's President Suleyman Demirel has accused the 
Swiss authorities of being responsible for the June attack by 
Kurdish extremists on the Turkish Embassy in Bern. Mr. Demirel 
said police had failed to provide sufficient security and were 
to blame for the incident in which one demonstrator was killed 
by shots fired from inside the embassy. He was speaking in 
Davos where he is attending the World Economic Forum. Swiss 
Foreign Minister Flavio Cotti denied there had been any security 
lapse. The shooting and Turkey's refusal to lift the diplomatic 
immunity of its embassy staff led to a diplomatic row between 
the two countries. 

</TEXT>

