<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   French Minister Criticizes U.S. Bosnia Policy at CSCE </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2801143094 Paris AFP in English 1419 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2801143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, Jan 28 (AFP) - Alain Lamassoure, France's 
junior minister of European affairs, implicitly criticized the 
U.S. rejection of a French peace initiative on Bosnia in a 
speech here before the CSCE, his office said Friday [28 January]. 
  "We sometimes have the feeling," Lamassoure told the 
Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe (CSCE) 
Thursday, "that other senior member states of the CSCE are not 
doing everything they could to encourage all parties involved to 
choose peace. 
  "Considering the point where we're at in the Yugoslav 
crisis, 
it is time for each of us to clearly take on some responsibility 
and choose, not only in words, but in action, the logic of 
peace." 
  Earlier this week, the U.S. rejected a French initiative for 
stiffer diplomatic and military action in Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

