<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EC To Assist With CIS Bank Clearing System </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701142694 Paris AFP in English 1819 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701142694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, Jan 26 (AFP) -- The European Community is 
to spend ECU2 million (2.2 million dollars) helping the 
countries of the former Soviet Union set up an efficient 
clearing system for banks, an EC official said here Wednesday 
[26 January]. 
  The main beneficiaries will be the Russian Central Bank and 
the new Interstate Bank, which is charged with establishing 
clearing houses for bank transactions throughout the 
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS). 
  The EC official said interbank transfers and payments were 
painfully slow in CIS countries, hindering trade. Citing one 
example, he said that a bank transfer from Vladivostok to Saint 
Petersburg could take weeks. 
  The EC's executive European Commission plans to send a team 
of high-level finance and banking specialists to Russia, 
Ukraine, and Belarus to counsel banks there. 

</TEXT>

