<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   World Economic Forum Session Continues in Davos </TI></H3>
<H4>   GATT Chief: Abolish G-7 </H4>
<F P=102> LD2801161194 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 1500 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2801161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Director-General of the GATT world trade body 
has called for the creation of a new global grouping to replace 
the Western-dominated Group of Seven industrialized nations. 
Peter Sutherland said the new body should be drawn from 
developing and former communist states as well as the 24 
developed nations in the Organization for Economic Cooperation 
and Development. He was speaking to leading economists from 
Europe and the United States who are attending the World 
Economic Forum in the Swiss resort of Davos. Mr Sutherland said 
it was not possible to continue with the majority of the world's 
people excluded from global economic management. Meanwhile 
economists have expressed differences over policies for reviving 
the struggling world economy 

</TEXT>

