<H3> <TI>   European, Belgian Officials Meet Cuba's Alarcon </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2801163394 Brussels BELGA in French 1503 GMT 28 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2801163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed JWI: "President of the Cuban National </F>
Assembly Calls For `Understanding' for Cuba"; as released by 
Brussels BELGA Database] 
  [Text] Brussels, 28 Jan (BELGA) -- Cuban National Assembly 
President Ricardo Alarcon, who has been in Belgium for several 
days, declared that the purpose of his visit was not to ask for 
anything but rather to try to acquaint his European partners 
better with the difficult situation of Cuba. 
  It should be remembered that Cuba is suffering a deep 
economic crisis due to the U.S. blockade and to the loss of its 
privileged contacts with countries of the East bloc. 
  At the end of a visit, during which he met, among others, 
European Commissioner for Development Cooperation Manuel Marin, 
European Parliament Chairman Egon Klepsch, and the presidents of 
the Belgian Chamber of Deputies and the Senate, 
Charles-Ferdinand Nothomb and Frank Swaelen, respectively, Mr. 
Alarcon indicated that Cuba was open to foreign investments, 
tourism, oil, and citrus fruit cultivation, and that any foreign 
investor would be allowed to own 100 percent of his company. 

</TEXT>

