<H3> <TI>   Number of Resettlers `Declined Strongly' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0102105394 Hamburg DPA in German 0954 GMT 1 Feb 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0102105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- In January the number of resettlers 
who came to Germany declined strongly compared with the previous 
month. According to an announcement by the Federal Interior 
Ministry on Tuesday [1 February], 18,827 persons -- including 
18,349 Russian Germans -- moved to the FRG. In December, the 
overall number was 27,043. 
  According to the Ministry, the number of applications for a 
notification of admission continues to decline: In January, 
22,517 ethnic Germans applied for resettlement; in the same 
month last year there were 28,731 applications. 
  Horst Waffenschmidt (Christian Democratic Union), 
parliamentary state secretary in the Interior Ministry, spoke of 
a "calming down": Obviously, the Germans now also see prospects 
for the future in the settlement areas in the Russian 
Federation. The FRG Government will continue to make efforts 
for improving living conditions there. However, the success 
primarily depends on the course of the restructuring process in 
the CIS states. 

</TEXT>

