<H3> <TI>   Ciampi Rules Out Running in Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR3101135094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1150 GMT 31 
Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR3101135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Ciampi Rules Out Running in </F>
Elections"] 
  [Text] Vienna, 31 Jan (ANSA) -- Italian Prime Minister 
Carlo Azeglio Ciampi said here today that he has no plans to 
stand in the general elections scheduled on March 27. 
  "My government's, and my own personal task are over," said 
the former long-serving governor of the Bank of Italy, who was 
brought in from that post to head the cabinet in April of last 
year. 
  Answering questions at a joint press conference with 
Austrian 
Chancellor Franz Vranitzky, Ciampi said his government had been 
set up to run the country until the approval and first 
application of the new electoral system. "Strong or less strong 
forms of renewal are to be found in all countries, and for 
neighbouring countries the question is to follow them and learn 
from them," commented Vranitzky. "I consider Ciampi as one of 
the fundamental promoters of renewal in Italy, whence I wish 
this renewal all possible success." 

</TEXT>

