<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Italy &amp; Vatican City </F>
<H3> <TI>   New `National Unity' Party Formed 28 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2801140294 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1206 GMT 28 
Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2801140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "New `National Unity' Party </F>
Announced"] 
  [Text] Rome, 28 Jan (ANSA) -- Yet another party is about to 
enter the increasingly crowded "moderate" area of the Italian 
political spectrum in the run-up to the March 27 elections. 
  A movement calling itself National Unity on Friday [28 
January] announced it will form an official party, grouping a 
wide array of moderate forces with the aim of "leading Italy out 
of the deep crisis in which it has sunk" through a "constituent 
legislature and executive." 
  The new party, its aims and its programs will be unveiled at 
a press conference Thursday, February 3 at the Rome press office 
in Piazza San Silvestro, a communique announced, adding that 
National Unity wants to help create an alliance between 
"political and cultural forces" from different backgrounds to 
give Italy a "modern political system truly based on 
alternatives, more freedom, more democracy and wider justice." 

</TEXT>

