<F P=100> UNITED KINGDOM </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cyprus' Mikhailidhis Confers at Foreign Office </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3101184794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3101184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis said that he 
has certified, from his contacts with the British Government, 
that London continues to emphasize a solution of the Cyprus 
issue and considers that the confidence-building measures are 
designed to create movement. Mikhailidhis also repeated the 
government's position that the confidence-building measures do 
not constitute a solution nor are they an aspect of a solution 
to the Cyprus issue. That it why, he said, no arrangement 
arising during implementation of the confidence-building 
measures should prejudge or influence the form of solution. 
  Mikhailidhis made the above statement following a meeting 
today in London with British Deputy Foreign Secretary David 
Amory. Mikhailidhis described his meeting with the British 
official as useful and constructive and added that his talks 
covered not only the confidence-building measures, but also the 
substance of the Cyprus issue. 

</TEXT>

